27/10/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer reaffirmed that the Pact's doors remain open to Albania, and urged the country to continue working towards the realisation of membership standards. During a meeting with Albanian Foreign Minister Besnik Mustafaj in Brussels on Wednesday (26 October), de Hoop Scheffer also acknowledged Albania's constructive role in the region, suggesting it would be helpful as the international community works to resolve the issue of Kosovo's status. 
Mustafaj also met with EU security chief Javier Solana, reiterating the government's commitment to implementing EU-related reforms and quickly completing talks on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement. (Albanian News - 27/10/05; NATO Web site - 26/10/05)
